# KC-ARCH-001 — Reliability & Persistence Standard

**Mandatory architecture policy.** Full text: `docs/architecture/kc-arch-001-reliability-persistence.md`

Every implementation prompt should assume:

> Implementation must comply with KC-ARCH-001 — Reliability & Persistence Standard.

## Do

- Await durable writes before success UI (`awaitQueuedWrite`, `confirmExecutionSaveFeedback`)
- Prefer per-entity Firestore docs with `ruknId`; else transactional merge; never LWW full replace on shared blobs
- Flush **latest cache** at queue execute time — never stale closed-over snapshots
- Ship schema + repository + `firestore.rules` together
- Map write failures with `toOperatorPersistError` / `formatPersistFailureBanner`
- Reuse `src/lib/reliability/*` and existing queue/merge helpers — no new persistence patterns
- Loading + success + failure + retry for every user-visible async path; no silent failures
- Assume concurrent Admins/Rukns; never wipe another user's data
- Emit structured write logs: module, operation, result, error code

## Do not

- Fire-and-forget for user-visible saves, then claim success
- Reuse `FRIENDLY_DATA_ACCESS_ERROR` ("Unable to load additional information") for writes
- Invent feature-specific persist/retry/error stacks
- Leave Security Rules misaligned with document shape

## Shared utilities

- `src/lib/reliability/persistErrors.ts`
- `src/lib/reliability/guidanceStateMerge.ts`
- `awaitQueuedWrite` in `src/repositories/firestore/firestoreRepositories.ts`
- `src/lib/executionPersistEvents.ts`
- Verify: `npm run verify:reliability`
